Did you use "Swap" or "Options"? Those work differently

OP: I used "Swap"

-------------------------------------

Swap is used to change courses, while Options is for changing sections within a course. Since you used swap it removed you from the class and re-enrolled you, which put you at the bottom of the waitlist. I'm not sure if there's anything you can do at this point though.

Hello,

I was enrolled in Prob 140 but attempted to swap my discussion section for a section at a different time, thinking CalCentral would keep me enrolled in my original class/discussion until I got off the waitlist for the new discussion (it normally does this when swapping a class for a different class). Instead it dropped me from the class and put me at the bottom of the waitlist (position 68), which I'm not sure I'll be able to get off of. Is there anything I can do about this?

Thanks.
